        android:fontFamily="sans-serif-condensed-medium"

        android:text="Nitrogen oxides come from car exhaust, coal power plants, and factory emissions. VOCs are released from gasoline, paints, and many cleaning solvents. When sunlight hits these chemicals, they form airborne particles and ground-level ozoneâ€”or smog."
